208
00:14:01,743 --> 00:14:02,073
I DID COME OUTSIDE.
Are you fine with
a loveless relationship?!

209
00:14:02,073 --> 00:14:03,303
Are you fine with
a loveless relationship?!

210
00:14:04,673 --> 00:14:06,573
Love comes later.

211
00:14:06,843 --> 00:14:10,403
People love themselves more
than anyone else.

212
00:14:10,613 --> 00:14:14,783
They end up loving those who
can fulfill the most desires they have.

213
00:14:15,083 --> 00:14:15,993
In a way, that's the truth.

214
00:14:15,993 --> 00:14:17,123
HIDEKI KASAI (45)
DIRECTOR
In a way, that's the truth.

215
00:14:17,123 --> 00:14:17,893
HIDEKI KASAI (45)
DIRECTOR
Huh?!

216
00:14:18,553 --> 00:14:21,683
Why not?
Let them get married, Take.

217
00:14:21,923 --> 00:14:23,733
Why don't we see where
a relationship

218
00:14:23,733 --> 00:14:25,493
between a bastard and
a fad follower will take them?

219
00:14:25,493 --> 00:14:26,763
This could be fun.

220
00:14:26,763 --> 00:14:28,753
Easy for you to say.

221
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:30,973
Anyway, we must discuss this
with the president.

222
00:14:30,973 --> 00:14:33,093
Until we do, please,
everyone, keep this a secret.

223
00:14:33,173 --> 00:14:34,343
What a pain.

224
00:14:34,343 --> 00:14:36,033
Let me do as I wish!
It's my marriage!

225
00:14:36,773 --> 00:14:39,303
Well then, let's get started
with the recording.

226
00:14:39,583 --> 00:14:40,843
Huh? Where's Reira?

227
00:14:41,513 --> 00:14:43,213
She was here until a moment ago.

228
00:14:43,413 --> 00:14:44,903
I'm sure she'll be right back.

229
00:14:45,613 --> 00:14:47,383
We record the vocals later anyway.

230
00:14:47,383 --> 00:14:48,913
We can do it without
temporary vocals.

231
00:14:52,023 --> 00:14:54,793
Mari, could you please
go look for her?

232
00:14:54,993 --> 00:14:55,653
Yes.

233
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:06,103
What? Reira's your real name?

234
00:15:06,603 --> 00:15:11,473
Mhm. Well, almost.
It's spelled L-A-Y-L-A.

235
00:15:11,973 --> 00:15:13,943
You know the Eric Clapton song, "Layla"?

236
00:15:14,113 --> 00:15:16,083
Yeah. It's a famous song.

237
00:15:16,713 --> 00:15:20,813
My father loved that song,
so he named me after it.

238
00:15:21,683 --> 00:15:23,693
Even now when I'm alone
in my room,

239
00:15:23,693 --> 00:15:27,593
I play that CD
and I don't feel alone.

240
00:15:29,193 --> 00:15:30,523
"Lovely Layla."

241
00:15:32,063 --> 00:15:33,623
The Japanese title is different...

242
00:15:34,563 --> 00:15:36,223
That'll be 5,500 yen.

243
00:15:43,773 --> 00:15:45,143
I'll be in touch.

244
00:16:06,503 --> 00:16:07,263
Yes?

245
00:16:10,373 --> 00:16:11,363
Hello?

246
00:16:14,473 --> 00:16:15,403
Hello?

247
00:16:16,573 --> 00:16:17,403
Shin, .,

248
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:18,503
What's the matter?

249
00:16:19,213 --> 00:16:21,773
Where are you now, Reira?
What about the recording?

