270
00:18:58,133 --> 00:18:59,573
Ah, sorry.

271
00:19:00,603 --> 00:19:01,903
Never mind.

272
00:19:02,713 --> 00:19:05,503
I'm used to your merciless oppression,

273
00:19:05,643 --> 00:19:07,733
and I covered for you at work.

274
00:19:08,143 --> 00:19:09,243
Where are you now?

275
00:19:15,653 --> 00:19:17,553
At Ren's... place?

276
00:19:18,093 --> 00:19:20,213
I'm guessing Ren's not there
because of work, right?

277
00:19:20,893 --> 00:19:22,363
I'm done with work today.

278
00:19:22,623 --> 00:19:25,353
What do you say we grab a bite
to eat before going to the studio?

279
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:26,593
Nobuo, .,

280
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:30,033
My treat! You've gotta let me
spill out my sad story!

281
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:33,633
I'm thinking, there really is
something wrong with me.

282
00:19:33,703 --> 00:19:35,833
I already know that, from long ago!

283
00:19:36,473 --> 00:19:40,033
I can't remember why I'm here.

284
00:19:41,383 --> 00:19:42,743
Am I still only half awake?

285
00:19:54,723 --> 00:19:59,323
The last thing I remember was the
strawberry glass about to roll off the table.

286
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:08,703
Those matching glasses were
the first things we bought together...

287
00:20:11,473 --> 00:20:14,503
Was I able to catch that glass...

288
00:20:15,743 --> 00:20:17,743
before it fell?

289
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:36,033
You know, Hachi...

290
00:20:36,973 --> 00:20:39,233
I was too small of a person

291
00:20:39,873 --> 00:20:42,033
to be able to accept everything
about you.

292
00:20:42,603 --> 00:20:44,773
I was like a cheap glass.

293
00:20:46,383 --> 00:20:50,843
It's just that I preferred the pain
of breaking into pieces,

294
00:20:51,653 --> 00:20:54,023
to the loneliness I felt
from losing everything.

295
00:20:54,023 --> 00:20:55,453
LOVELY LAYLA
